Class RnnOutputLayer

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Classifier, Layer, Model

    public class RnnOutputLayer
extends BaseOutputLayer<RnnOutputLayer>
    Recurrent Neural Network Output Layer.
    Handles calculation of gradients etc for various objective functions.
    Functionally the same as OutputLayer, but handles output and label reshaping automatically.
    Input and output activations are same as other RNN layers: 3 dimensions with shape [miniBatchSize,nIn,timeSeriesLength] and [miniBatchSize,nOut,timeSeriesLength] respectively.
    See Also:
    BaseOutputLayer, OutputLayer, Serialized Form

        Calculate the gradient relative to the error in the next layer
        Specified by:

        backpropGradient in class BaseOutputLayer<RnnOutputLayer>
        Parameters:
        epsilon - w^(L+1)*delta^(L+1). Or, equiv: dC/da, i.e., (dC/dz)*(dz/da) = dC/da, where C is cost function a=sigma(z) is activation.
        Returns:
        Pair where Gradient is gradient for this layer, INDArray is epsilon needed by next layer, but before element-wise multiply by sigmaPrime(z). So for standard feed-forward layer, if this layer is L, then return.getSecond() == (w^(L)*(delta^(L))^T)^T
